# apps/web environment — all optional.
#
# --- Local dev (`npm run dev`) ---
# Works with NO config: the Vite /boring proxy forwards to the public, token-less
# boringd endpoint (https://162-43-188-89.sslip.io). No SSH tunnel needed.
#
# To target a different boringd (e.g. an SSH tunnel to a private box):
#   ssh -N -L 18080:localhost:8080 root@<box-ip> -i ~/.ssh/boring_latitude
#   BORING_URL=http://localhost:18080 BORING_TOKEN=<token-if-any> npm run dev -w web
# BORING_URL=http://localhost:18080
# BORING_TOKEN=
#
# --- Production (set on the Vercel project, not here) ---
# The browser talks to boringd directly (the TTY/VNC/agent are WebSockets and
# can't go through a serverless function):
#   PUBLIC_BORING_URL=https://162-43-188-89.sslip.io
#
# We use the sslip.io host (it encodes the box IP and resolves straight to the
# box) instead of api.boringcomputers.com, which Vercel's DNS management
# intermittently intercepts. Deploy + promote the domains in one step with:
#   bash infra/latitude/deploy-web.sh
